-- Slovakia Considers Higher Retirement Age, Hospodarske Says
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-04-18T06:48:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/slovakia-considers-higher-retirement-age-hospodarske-says.html
The Slovak government is
considering increasing the official retirement age to keep it in
line with lengthening  life expectancy ,  Hospodarske Noviny 
reported, citing Labor Minister Jan Richter.  Retirement age, currently set at 62, would start gradually
rising in 2016 to reach 64 years in 2030, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
